      "about": ["agent.beta"],
      "tags": ["long", "investigation", "restart"],
      "body": "The controlled restart investigation compared service readiness, credential restoration, token refresh scheduling, and the first authenticated request. Readiness became healthy before the credential cache was hydrated. The token refresh worker started later and the first request entered a race with restoration. Repeating the test with an explicit credential-ready barrier removed the failure. The durable recommendation is to keep readiness separate from credential readiness, expose both states, and prevent authenticated traffic until the credential barrier completes. This record is intentionally longer than the other fixtures so deterministic chunk boundaries and cross-chunk retrieval are exercised without containing production data."
    },
